Printer ink cartridges are one of the biggest scams going.. Way more expensive than they should be. The lengths manufacturers go to in order to force you to buy their own branded cartridges is outrageous. On the subject of UV ink.. I'm a bookworm, but I like to make notes or highlight passages in my books, and filling a book with such notes does kinda spoil it for others reading that book. So what I do now is make those notes with security markers, or UV visible ink pens. It leaves the book looking untouched, and I can still see my notes with a UV torch. You can even buy ballpoints that use this ink now, they have a button cell powered LED in their caps. Gotta love technology! :)
